============================= Database Cleanup Utility ==========================================

==>Overview

This utility is designed to clean up automation-created test data from the MySQL database.
It safely deletes all records related to automation test execution, including:

Agents
Managers
Venues
Tournaments
Players
Teams
Matches
Related child records (comments, balls, squad data, stats, assignments, etc.)

Important:
This script deletes only data created for automation purposes (based on naming patterns like %Automation%).
Production or real user data will NOT be affected if naming conventions are followed properly.

===================================================================================================================

cleanup/
│
├── CleanupQueries.java   -> Contains all DELETE query constants
├── DBUtils.java          -> Handles MySQL database connection
└── DbCleanup.java        -> Main class to execute cleanup script


*********************************The script removes automation-related data from****************************

user (Agents / Managers created via automation)
match_assign_user
comments
pending_balls
archived_pending_balls
tournament
tournament_venues
tournament_teams
tournament_player_stats
venues
team
player
team_player
squad
squad_team_players
squad_match_players
balls
history_balls
schedules
matches




================================================================================================================
Update database credentials inside DBUtils.java

jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/your_database
